q:
Sort the functions in ascending order of asymptotic (Big-O) complexity:
$f_1(n) = n$, $f_2(n) = 80$, $f_3(n) = n^{\log n}$, $f_4(n) = (\log(\log n))^2$, $f_5(n) = (\log n)^{\log n}$

Consider two functions $f(n) = 10n + 2\log n$ and $g(n) = 5n + 2(\log n)^2$. Which of the following is correct? (Note: This was a Multiple Select Question with A and B as correct options. $\Theta$ is the tightest bound.)

The function $h(n) = f(n)/g(n)$ where $f(n) = \sqrt{n}$ and $g(n) = n\log n + n$. How many of the following relations are correct for $h(n)$? 
I. $h(n) = o(n^{-1/2})$, II. $h(n) = O(n^{-1/2})$, III. $h(n) = \Omega(1/\log n)$, IV. $h(n) = \Theta(n^{-1/2})$
Consider the asymptotic functions: $f_1 = 2^n$, $f_2 = (1.001)^n$, $f_3 = e^n$, $f_4 = n!$. Which of the following is the correct increasing order of growth?

Consider the functions: $f_1(n) = 4^{2n}$, $f_2(n) = n!$, $f_3(n) = 4^{e^n}$, $f_4(n) = n^{n^n}$. Which of the following is/are correct? (This was a Multiple Select Question, B, C, and D are correct. We use B as the single answer index.)
Consider two functions $f_1(n) = n^{2^n}$ and $f_2(n) = n^{n^2}$. Which of the following is true?

The function $f(n) = \sum_{i=1}^n i^3 = x$. Which of the following asymptotic relations for $x$ are correct?
I. $\Theta(n^4)$, II. $\Theta(n^5)$, III. $O(n^5)$, IV. $\Omega(n^3)$
